<BODY text=3D#000000 bgColor=3D#ffffff>
<P>This is how to make a sample demo based on Swimmer(c) Tehkan<BR>All =
the gfx=20
were ripped for the game under MAME and are copyright Tehkan<BR>I don't =
use them=20
for commercial use and give all the needed credit so i hope it's not =
illegal=20
</P>All the gfx are 16colors bmp and with the correct =
background/transparent=20
color (color 0)=20
<P><B><FONT size=3D4>1/ Background</FONT></B></P><IMG=20
src=3D"file:///E:/Dev_c/sega/bmp2Tile_ex/_doc/back.gif">=20
<P>Our background is the full screen game without sprites<BR>As you can =
see, for=20
a 256x244 pic, it is full of the same tiles (full, full gray-green,=20
boder..)<BR>Yes, you got it...we need an optimized map!<BR>So load the =
pic under=20
Bmp2Tile and<BR>- Save the palette (File &gt; Save Pal &gt; Asm)<BR>- =
Select all=20
(* key)<BR>- Save an optimized map...and, why not, compressed (File &gt; =
Save=20
Map &gt; Binary Optimized Compressed)<BR><BR>Et voil=E0! You have an =
assembler=20
file which include 2 binaries (1 for the map def and 1 for the =
compressed tiles)=20
and all the def needed (pal, size, number of tiles)=20
<P><B><FONT size=3D4>2/ Tree</FONT></B></P><IMG=20
src=3D"file:///E:/Dev_c/sega/bmp2Tile_ex/_doc/tree.gif">=20
<P>Let's add a tree that we can put where we want on the screen<BR>So =
load the=20
pic under Bmp2Tile and<BR>- Save the palette (File &gt; Save Pal &gt; =
Asm)<BR>-=20
Select all ('*' key)<BR>- Resize the selector if you think the last line =
isn't=20
useful (i did it) ('g' key)<BR>- Save a compressed tile (File &gt; Save =
Tile=20
&gt; Binary Compressed)<BR>You have an assembler file which include a =
binary and=20
all the def needed=20
<P><B><FONT size=3D4>3/ Swimmer</FONT></B></P><IMG alt=3D"Frame 0"=20
src=3D"file:///E:/Dev_c/sega/bmp2Tile_ex/_doc/swimmer0.gif">&nbsp;&nbsp;<=
IMG=20
alt=3D"Frame 1" =
src=3D"file:///E:/Dev_c/sega/bmp2Tile_ex/_doc/swimmer1.gif">=20
<P>Now, convert our swimmer<BR>He has 2 frames : swimmer0 when no swim =
and=20
swimmer1 when he is swimming<BR>Load the pic of frame 0 under Bmp2Tile =
and<BR>-=20
Save the palette (File &gt; Save Pal &gt; Asm)<BR>- Select all ('*' =
key)<BR>-=20
Resize the selector to have a 2x4 sprites (i "forgot" to delete the last =
column)=20
('t' key)<BR>- Switch to Sprite mode (<B>VERY IMPORTANT</B>) (Options =
&gt;=20
Output mode &gt; Sprite)<BR>- Save a tile (File &gt; Save Tile &gt;=20
Binary)<BR>Load the pic of frame 1 under Bmp2Tile and<BR>- Select all =
('*'=20
key)<BR>- Save a tile (File &gt; Save Tile &gt; Binary)<BR>You have 2 =
assembler=20
file which include a binary and all the def needed Join the 2 in an only =
one=20
swimmer.s=20
<P><B><FONT size=3D4>4/ Hints</FONT></B></P>Rename the assembler file in =
.ASM to=20
make a difference between a JAS file (.s) and a Maccer filer =
(.asm)<BR>Write the=20
exact size of the compressed tile files (look at properties of the =
file), it's=20
needed for the uncompress function=20
<P><B><FONT size=3D4>5/ Final words</FONT></B></P>
<P>The source of the demo is commented so i think you'll =
understand<BR>Share all=20
you make! if not public, at least email me a private url to download =
your=20
work!<BR>I can be reached at <A=20
href=3D"http://www.consoledev.fr.st/">http://www.consoledev.fr.st/</A><BR=
></P>
